<h2>Top Picks Explained:</h2>
<p><iframe data-cliversesrc="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Ao5B00KytUA" width="700" height="400" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start"></span></iframe></p>
<h2>What To Look For When Buying A Cat Bed?</h2>
<p>Cats have a tendency to sleep in strange places  anywhere except where you want them to. This makes finding a bed your cat will sleep in a difficult task. Fortunately, weve done the hard work for you in testing and researching some of the top cat beds on the market to help you make the right choice.</p>
<p><strong>Here is what our checklist looked like as we searched for the elusive perfect cat bed:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Comfort</strong>  Whats the point of a cat bed if it isnt comfortable? We looked for a cat bed that was designed to accommodate various sleeping positions and was made from soft materials with the right amount of padding for optimal comfort.</li>
<li><strong>Durability</strong> &#8211; Each kitty has a different personality and some are more playful than others. Some cats have a <a href="https://allaboutcats.com/how-to-stop-your-cat-scratching-furniture" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tendency to scratch</a> and others like to knead before they settle down. We looked for a cat bed that was made from durable materials to withstand a cats sharp claws.</li>
<li><strong>Easy to Clean</strong>  As a cat owner, everything you own is probably already covered in cat hair. We looked for a bed that was easy to clean, paying particular attention to models with removable covers that make them machine washable.</li>
<li><strong>Support</strong>  As your cat gets older, his joints may start to ache and he may develop <a href="https://allaboutcats.com/arthritis-in-cats" target="_blank" rel="noopener">issues like arthritis</a> that can make it difficult for him to sleep comfortably. We looked for a cat bed that offered support both in the base and around the edges for cats who need it.</li>
<li><strong>Price</strong>  Everything comes with a price, but you dont necessarily need to spend a small fortune to find a bed your cat will love. We tested cat beds on all levels of the price spectrum.</li>
<li><strong>Customer Service</strong> &#8211; Our reasoning here? Good customer service goes hand-in-hand with quality products. If theres an issue with the bed, you want to know theres someone you can contact.</li>
</ul>
<p>We found the following products to be our top picks for the most loved cat beds. Hope this helps in your search for a suitable bed for your cat!</p>
<h2>The Top 12 Best Cat Beds On The Market</h2>
