<h2 id="embracepetinsurancegopetplan" style="text-align: center;"><span class="product-review-heading">#1 </span>Best Heated Bed: K&amp;H Thermo Kitty Cat Bed</h2>
<p><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-30773 aligncenter" src="https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/KH-Pet-Products-Thermo-Kitty-Cat-Bed.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="283" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="amz" href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:best-cat-bed/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fkh-pet-products-thermo-kitty-cat-bed%2Fdp%2F54490" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noreferrer noopener">View On Chewy</a> <a class="amz" href="https://www.amazon.com/Pet-Products-Thermo-Kitty-Heated-Mocha/dp/B07HML9YLD/?tag=wwwallabou001-20" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noreferrer noopener">View On Amazon</a></p>
<p>Available in two different sizes, this circular cat bed features an integrated heating pad that warms the surface of the bed 10 to 15 degrees above the ambient temperature in the room. This puts the bed roughly in the same temperature range as your cats body temperature.</p>
<p>This heated cat bed is perfect for colder climates or for winter use, though theres nothing to stop your cat from using it all year-round. It features a thick orthopedic foam base to make it extra comfy and to provide an added degree of support for cats who have joint issues. Plus, the removable cover is machine washable, just be sure you hang it up to dry.</p>
<p>In terms of potential downsides for this cat bed, the raised edges may be a little high for cats with mobility issues. Additionally, because it is a heated bed, you may be limited in terms of location because it needs to be close enough to an outlet that you can plug it in.</p>
<h3>Pros</h3>
<ul class="pro">
<li>Orthopedic foam base for comfort</li>
<li>Raised edges and round shape perfect for cuddling</li>
<li>Integrated heater keeps the bed warm</li>
<li>Available in two different sizes</li>
</ul>
<h3>Cons</h3>
<ul class="con">
<li>Raised edges may be an issue for some cats</li>
